The paper deals with the MaxClique problem, which is a well-known problem in computer science and graph theory. The paper discusses algorithmic approaches and probabilistic methods to solve the problem, which are common topics in the sub-categories of cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). However, since the paper focuses on finding an approximate solution within a factor of 2 of the known limit, it is more likely to belong to cs.DM and cs.AI, which deal with optimization problems and heuristic algorithms.
